{"type":"message","id":"9a9c2074","parentId":"0a131bd0","timestamp":"2026-06-13T03:11:41.025Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"568c642b785344c3b72bb2e1e8fc04b4","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"searchQueries\": [\n    \"PyTorch TensorFlow ML engineering MLOps tools frameworks development news latest\"\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2229,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8ad91010ecc5d466\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMachine Learning Engineer - Mawdoo3 - OpenTalent\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8ad91010ecc5d466\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"http://opentalent.in/jobs/machine-learning-engineer-mawdoo3\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2e3e92b04469fab\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n3+ years of experience in machine learning engineering · Proficiency in Python and ML frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch) · Experience with MLOps\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2e3e92b04469fab\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"opentalent.in\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2e3e92b04469fab\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n3+ years of experience in machine learning engineering · Proficiency in Python and ML frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch) · Experience with MLOps\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2e3e92b04469fab\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f5e49114359c54ee\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - tensorflow/tensorflow: An Open Source Machine Learning Framework for Everyone · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f5e49114359c54ee\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a90c4b360d1a62fb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* Code of conduct\\n* Contributing\\n* Apache-2.0 license\\n* Security\\n\\n[](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/4b99b5f67e5e01f9ba4d88092d59b81a473b8f8fba65b8d3b5dd638fafdcee58/68747470733a2f2f7777772e74656e736f72666c6f772e6f72672f696d616765732f74665f6c6f676f5f686f72697a6f6e74616c2e706e67)\\n\\n[Python](https://badge.fury.io/py/tensorflow) [PyPI](https://badge.fury.io/py/tensorflow) [DOI](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4724125) [CII Best Practices](https://bestpractices.coreinfrastructure.org/projects/1486) [OpenSSF Scorecard](https://securityscorecards.dev/viewer/?uri=github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow) [Fuzzing Status](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/list?sort=-opened&can=1&q=proj:tensorflow) [Fuzzing Status](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/list?sort=-opened&can=1&q=proj:tensorflow-py) [OSSRank](https://ossrank.com/p/44) Contributor Covenant\\n\\n|**`Documentation`** |\\n| --- |\\n|[Documentation](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/) |\\n\\n[TensorFlow](https://www.tensorflow.\\norg/) is an end-to-end open source platform\\nfor machine learning. It has a comprehensive, flexible ecosystem of [tools](https://www.tensorflow.org/resources/tools) , [libraries](https://www.tensorflow.org/resources/libraries-extensions) , and [community](https://www.tensorflow.org/community) resources that lets\\nresearchers push the state-of-the-art in ML and developers easily build and\\ndeploy ML-powered applications.\\n\\nTensorFlow was originally developed by researchers and engineers working within\\nthe Machine Intelligence team at Google Brain to conduct research in machine\\nlearning and neural networks. However, the framework is versatile enough to be\\nused in other areas as well.\\n\\nTensorFlow provides stable [Python](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python) and [C++](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/cc) APIs, as well as a\\nnon-guaranteed backward compatible API for [other languages](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs) .\\nKeep up-to-date with release announcements and security updates by subscribing\\nto [announce@tensorflow.org](https://groups.google.com/a/tensorflow.org/forum/#!forum/announce) .\\nSee all the [mailing lists](https://www.tensorflow.org/community/forums) .\\n\\n## Install\\n\\nSee the [TensorFlow install guide](https://www.tensorflow.org/install) for the [pip package](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/pip) , to [enable GPU support](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu) , use a [Docker container](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/docker) , and [build from source](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/source) .\\n\\nTo install the current release, which includes support for [CUDA-enabled GPU cards](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu) _(Ubuntu and Windows)_ :\\n\\n```\\n pip install tensorflow\\n```\\n\\nOther devices (DirectX and MacOS-metal) are supported using [Device Plugins](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu_plugins) .\\n\\nA smaller CPU-only TensorFlow package is also available:\\n\\n```\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a90c4b360d1a62fb\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a90c4b360d1a62fb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* Code of conduct\\n* Contributing\\n* Apache-2.0 license\\n* Security\\n\\n[](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/4b99b5f67e5e01f9ba4d88092d59b81a473b8f8fba65b8d3b5dd638fafdcee58/68747470733a2f2f7777772e74656e736f72666c6f772e6f72672f696d616765732f74665f6c6f676f5f686f72697a6f6e74616c2e706e67)\\n\\n[Python](https://badge.fury.io/py/tensorflow) [PyPI](https://badge.fury.io/py/tensorflow) [DOI](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4724125) [CII Best Practices](https://bestpractices.coreinfrastructure.org/projects/1486) [OpenSSF Scorecard](https://securityscorecards.dev/viewer/?uri=github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow) [Fuzzing Status](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/list?sort=-opened&can=1&q=proj:tensorflow) [Fuzzing Status](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/list?sort=-opened&can=1&q=proj:tensorflow-py) [OSSRank](https://ossrank.com/p/44) Contributor Covenant\\n\\n|**`Documentation`** |\\n| --- |\\n|[Documentation](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/) |\\n\\n[TensorFlow](https://www.tensorflow.\\norg/) is an end-to-end open source platform\\nfor machine learning. It has a comprehensive, flexible ecosystem of [tools](https://www.tensorflow.org/resources/tools) , [libraries](https://www.tensorflow.org/resources/libraries-extensions) , and [community](https://www.tensorflow.org/community) resources that lets\\nresearchers push the state-of-the-art in ML and developers easily build and\\ndeploy ML-powered applications.\\n\\nTensorFlow was originally developed by researchers and engineers working within\\nthe Machine Intelligence team at Google Brain to conduct research in machine\\nlearning and neural networks. However, the framework is versatile enough to be\\nused in other areas as well.\\n\\nTensorFlow provides stable [Python](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python) and [C++](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/cc) APIs, as well as a\\nnon-guaranteed backward compatible API for [other languages](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs) .\\nKeep up-to-date with release announcements and security updates by subscribing\\nto [announce@tensorflow.org](https://groups.google.com/a/tensorflow.org/forum/#!forum/announce) .\\nSee all the [mailing lists](https://www.tensorflow.org/community/forums) .\\n\\n## Install\\n\\nSee the [TensorFlow install guide](https://www.tensorflow.org/install) for the [pip package](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/pip) , to [enable GPU support](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu) , use a [Docker container](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/docker) , and [build from source](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/source) .\\n\\nTo install the current release, which includes support for [CUDA-enabled GPU cards](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu) _(Ubuntu and Windows)_ :\\n\\n```\\n pip install tensorflow\\n```\\n\\nOther devices (DirectX and MacOS-metal) are supported using [Device Plugins](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/gpu_plugins) .\\n\\nA smaller CPU-only TensorFlow package is also available:\\n\\n```\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a90c4b360d1a62fb\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8422dfe2af37f362\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Development Frameworks in 2025: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras & JAX | by Amit Kharche | Medium\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8422dfe2af37f362\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/%40amitkharche/ai-development-frameworks-in-2025-tensorflow-pytorch-keras-jax-d2eb8ffd06e9\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf9cf685fddff53a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSitemap\\n\\n[Open in app](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.medium.reader&referrer=utm_source%3DmobileNavBar&source=post_page---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------------------------)\\n\\nGet app\\n\\nWrite\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n# AI Development Frameworks in 2025: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras & JAX\\n\\nAmit Kharche\\n\\n4 min read\\n\\n·\\n\\nMay 19, 2025\\n\\n\\\\--\\n\\nListen\\n\\nShare\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n**_Strengths, Production Readiness, Hardware Compatibility, and Ecosystem Tools_**\\n\\n## Why Frameworks Matter in AI Model Development\\n\\nThe choice of AI framework can significantly influence how quickly you prototype, how well your model generalizes, and how smoothly it gets deployed at scale.\\n\\nA good framework:\\n\\n* **Enables fast experimentation**\\n* **Supports model interpretability and debugging**\\n* **Integrates with hardware (GPU/TPU/Edge)**\\n* **Ensures scalable deployment and maintenance**\\nThink of AI frameworks like vehicles, some are built for speed (research), others for endurance (production), and some try to balance both.\\n\\n## Frameworks Compared: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras (tf.keras), and JAX\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n## Model Complexity vs. Generalization\\n\\nThe tension between model complexity and generalization is one of the core challenges in AI development.\\n\\n* **Underfitting** = model is too simple\\n* **Overfitting** = model is too complex\\n* **Good fit** = model captures patterns without memorizing\\n\\n### Visualized: Polynomial Regression Example\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n## Hardware Compatibility Table\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n**JAX is ideal for high-speed research on TPUs/GPUs** , but lacks native mobile or edge deployment tools.\\n\\n## Production Readiness & Benchmarks (2025)\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\\\*Based on public benchmarks and TPU/GPU performance tests. Numbers vary by model architecture and hardware type.\\n\\n> PyTorch has caught up significantly with TorchServe and ONNX. TensorFlow still leads in optimized deployment pipelines.\\n> \\n>\\n\\n## Debugging, Visualization, & Monitoring Tools\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n> _For PyTorch, use torchviz or export to ONNX and visualize via Netron._\\n> \\n>\\n\\n## Sample Neural Network in Each Framework\\n\\n### TensorFlow + Keras\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n### PyTorch\\n\\n### JAX + Flax\\n\\n## Learning Paths by Framework\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n**Complexity Note:** PyTorch offers more intuitive syntax but requires deeper code control. TensorFlow has steeper learning curves in production (TFX). JAX requires strong math and functional programming skills.\\n\\n## Ecosystem Evolution Trends (2025+)\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n## When to Choose What?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf9cf685fddff53a\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"medium.com\",\n      \"published\": \"2025-08-27\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf9cf685fddff53a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSitemap\\n\\n[Open in app](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.medium.reader&referrer=utm_source%3DmobileNavBar&source=post_page---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------------------------)\\n\\nGet app\\n\\nWrite\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n# AI Development Frameworks in 2025: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras & JAX\\n\\nAmit Kharche\\n\\n4 min read\\n\\n·\\n\\nMay 19, 2025\\n\\n\\\\--\\n\\nListen\\n\\nShare\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n**_Strengths, Production Readiness, Hardware Compatibility, and Ecosystem Tools_**\\n\\n## Why Frameworks Matter in AI Model Development\\n\\nThe choice of AI framework can significantly influence how quickly you prototype, how well your model generalizes, and how smoothly it gets deployed at scale.\\n\\nA good framework:\\n\\n* **Enables fast experimentation**\\n* **Supports model interpretability and debugging**\\n* **Integrates with hardware (GPU/TPU/Edge)**\\n* **Ensures scalable deployment and maintenance**\\nThink of AI frameworks like vehicles, some are built for speed (research), others for endurance (production), and some try to balance both.\\n\\n## Frameworks Compared: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras (tf.keras), and JAX\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\\n\\n## Model Complexity vs. Generalization\\n\\nThe tension between model complexity and generalization is one of the core challenges in AI development.\\n\\n* **Underfitting** = model is too simple\\n* **Overfitting** = model is too complex\\n* **Good fit** = model captures patterns without memorizing\\n\\n### Visualized: Polynomial Regression Example\\n\\nPress enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image 